      "content": "it wasn't like a migraine or anything, i've never had vision issues before. it was so... mathematical. the way the light hit the \"duplicate\" part of the wall was identical, down to the exact same shadow angle. it didn't feel like my eyes were failing, it felt like the world just missed a frame or something. have you heard anything about simulation theory or like, glitches in reality? i feel like i'm losing my mind but it felt too real to just be a hallucination.",
